bayStackLldpExtMedMib.name: bayStackLldpExtMedMib
bayStackLldpExtMedMib.description: This MIB module is an extension to the standard LLDP-EXT-MED MIB.

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyTable.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyTable
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyTable.description: This table contains one row per policy type per port of media policy information (as a part of the MED organizational extension) on the local system known to this agent.

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyEntry.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyEntry
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyEntry.description: Information about a particular policy on a specific port component.

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyAppType.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyAppType
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyAppType.description: The media type that defines the primary function of the application for the policy advertised by an endpoint.

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyVlanID.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyVlanID
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyVlanID.description: An extension of the VLAN Identifier for the port, as defined in IEEE 802.1P-1998. A value of 1 through 4094 is used to define a valid PVID. A value of 0 shall be used if the device is using priority tagged frames, meaning that only the 802.1p priority level is significant and the default VID of the ingress port is being used instead. A value of 4095 is reserved for implementation use.

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyPriority.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyPriority
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyPriority.description: This object contains the value of the 802.1p priority which is associated with the given port on the local system.

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyDscp.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyDscp
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyDscp.description: This object contains the value of the Differentiated Service Code Point (DSCP) as defined in IETF RFC 2474 and RFC 2475 which is associated with the given port on the local system.

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyUnknown.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyUnknown
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyUnknown.description: A value of 'true' indicates that the network policy for the specified application type is currently unknown. In this case, the VLAN ID, the layer 2 priority and the DSCP value fields are ignored. A value of 'false' indicates that this network policy is defined

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyTagged.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyTagged
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyTagged.description: A value of 'true' indicates that the application is using a tagged VLAN. A value of 'false' indicates that for the specific application the device either is using an untagged VLAN or does not support port based VLAN operation. In this case, both the VLAN ID and the Layer 2 priority fields are ignored and only the DSCP value has relevance

bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyRowStatus.name: bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyRowStatus
bsLldpXMedLocMediaPolicyRowStatus.description: This object is used to create/delete entries in this table. Note that all columns in an entry must be set before an entry can be made valid. Also note that while an entry is valid, any column in the entry may be modified.
